UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 33
1 (b) Publicly owned county jail or regional jail vehicles shall not be equipped with
2 or use a siren, whistle, or bell.
3 (c) The equipment prescribed by this subsection shall be in addition to any other
4 equipment required by the motor vehicle laws.
5 (7) Red flashing lights may be used by school buses.
6 (8) No emergency vehicle, public safety vehicle, or any other vehicle covered by KRS
7 189.910 to 189.950 shall use any light of any other color than those specified by
8 KRS 189.910 to 189.950. Sirens, whistles, and bells may not be used by vehicles
9 other than those specified by KRS 189.910 to 189.950, except that any vehicle may
10 be equipped with a theft alarm signal device which is so arranged that it cannot be
11 used by the driver as an ordinary warning signal.
12 (9) Vehicles used as command posts at incidents may be equipped with and use when
13 on scene, a green rotating, oscillating, or flashing light. This light shall be in
14 addition to the lights and sirens required in this section.
15 (10) A personal vehicle used by a paid or volunteer firefighter, ambulance personnel, or
16 emergency services director who is responding to an emergency shall display the
17 lights required in subsection (1) of this section.
18 (11) An elected coroner may equip a publicly or privately owned motor vehicle, or both,
19 with flashing, rotating, or oscillating red and blue lights and a siren meeting the
20 requirements of this section solely for the purpose of responding to a report of the
21 death of a human being subject to the following terms and conditions:
22 (a) The coroner makes a written request to the legislative body of the county,
23 urban-county government, charter county government, consolidated local
24 government, or unified local government in which the coroner was elected to
25 equip a publicly or privately owned motor vehicle, or both, with flashing,
26 rotating, or oscillating red and blue lights and a siren meeting the
27 requirements of this section, and that request is approved by the legislative
