UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 33
1 body by ordinance or by court order;
2 (b) The coroner may use the lights and siren only while responding to the scene
3 of the report of a death of a human being and shall not, KRS 189.940 to the
4 contrary notwithstanding, exceed the posted speed limit; and
5 (c) The permission granted pursuant to this section shall expire upon the coroner
6 leaving office or the legislative body revoking the authorization.
7 (12) A deputy coroner certified pursuant to KRS Chapter 72 may equip a publicly
8 owned or privately owned motor vehicle, or both, with flashing, rotating, or
9 oscillating red and blue lights and a siren meeting the requirements of this section
10 solely for the purpose of responding to a report of the death of a human being,
11 subject to the following terms and conditions:
12 (a) The deputy coroner has made a written request to the coroner to equip a
13 publicly owned or privately owned vehicle with flashing, rotating, or
14 oscillating red and blue lights meeting the requirements of this section and the
15 coroner has approved the request in writing;
16 (b) The coroner makes a written request to the legislative body of the county,
17 urban-county government, charter county government, consolidated local
18 government, or unified local government in which the coroner is elected to
19 permit the deputy coroner to equip a publicly owned motor vehicle or
20 privately owned motor vehicle, or both, and that request has been approved by
21 the legislative body by ordinance or by court order;
22 (c) The deputy coroner may use the lights and siren only while responding to the
23 scene of the report of the death of a human being and shall not, KRS 189.940
24 to the contrary notwithstanding, exceed the posted speed limit; and
25 (d) The permission granted pursuant to this section shall expire upon the coroner
26 leaving office or the legislative body revoking the authorization.
27 Section 2. This Act may be cited as Troy's Law.
